2. Plotting Contig N50 with respect to First Publication Date¶

Objective:¶

Using matplotlib.pyplot and our pandas DataFrame, create a scatter plot for the contig N50 for each assembly with respect to the initial publication date. Create a bar plot to show the number of deposited assemblies per month as well as a line plot to show the change in sequencing cost over time.

# Read in the csv containing sequencing cost data over time. Prepare the data for plotting. 
sequencing_costs = pd.read_csv('sequencing_cost_data.csv')
sequencing_costs = (sequencing_costs.dropna(axis = 0, how = 'all')
                                    .dropna(axis = 1, how = 'all'))
sequencing_costs.Date = sequencing_costs.Date.astype('datetime64[s]')
In [7]:
# Create a dictionary containing the corresponding colours for long and short read data
color_map = {'Long read' : '#ffd966',
             'Short read' : '#0da5f7', 
             'No information provided' : '#dddddd'}
In [8]:
## Set up plotting 
plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 500 
fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, sharex = True, gridspec_kw = {'height_ratios': [2.5, 7]})
fig.subplots_adjust(hspace = 0.07)
fig.suptitle('Spiralia Genome Contig N50 by Submission Date', y = 0.95, fontsize = 11) 

## Set up x axis: 
years = np.arange(2002, 2023, 2) 
years = np.array([datetime.date(year, 1, 1) for year in years])
axs[1].set_xticks(years) 
axs[1].set_xlabel('Submission Date', fontsize = 8) 

## Bar plot for genomes deposited with respect to time 
axs[0].set_ylabel('Total deposited', fontsize = 8) 
counts = metadata.groupby(pd.Grouper(key = 'First_Publication_Date', freq = 'M')).size() 
axs[0].bar(counts.index, counts.values, width = 25, color = '#aaaaaa') 

## Line plot for sequencing cost over time 
ax = axs[0].twinx() 

ax.set_ylabel('Cost per Mb', fontsize = 8) 
ax.set_yscale('log') 
ax.get_yaxis().get_major_formatter().useOffset = False 
ax.plot(sequencing_costs.Date, sequencing_costs['Cost per Mb'], 
        linewidth = 0.5, 
        linestyle = '--', 
        color = 'black') 

## Scatter plot Contig N50 with respect to first publication date 
axs[1].set_ylabel('Contig N50', fontsize = 8) 
axs[1].set_yscale('log') 
axs[1].axhline(y=100000, linewidth = 0.5, 
        linestyle = '--', 
        color = 'black')

for sequencing_type in ('No information provided', 'Short read', 'Long read'): 
    axs[1].scatter(x = metadata.loc[metadata.Sequencing_Type == sequencing_type, 'First_Publication_Date'], 
               y = metadata.loc[metadata.Sequencing_Type == sequencing_type, 'Original_Contig_N50'], 
               c = color_map[sequencing_type], 
               marker = 'o', s = 50, 
               edgecolors = 'black', 
               linewidths = 0.4) 

ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)
axs[0].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)
axs[1].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)
In [9]:
# Save the figure as a pdf 
fig.savefig('Contig_N50_wrt_Time.pdf', transparent=True, format = 'pdf')

# Find the corresponding accessions for the species in the list. 
# Print species not found in the metadata. 
accessions_to_label = list() 
for label in to_label: 
    if label in list(metadata.Organism_Name): 
        accession = metadata.loc[metadata.Organism_Name == label].index.values[0]
        accessions_to_label.append(accession)
    else: 
        print(f'{label} not in metadata')

## Set up plotting

fig.subplots_adjust(hspace = 0.07)
fig.suptitle('Spiralia Genome Contig N50 by Submission Date', y = 0.95, fontsize = 11) 

## Set up x axis: 
years = np.arange(2002, 2023, 2) 
years = np.array([datetime.date(year, 1, 1) for year in years])
axs[1].set_xticks(years) 
axs[1].set_xlabel('Submission Date', fontsize = 8) 

## Bar plot for genomes deposited with respect to time 
axs[0].set_ylabel('Total deposited', fontsize = 8) 
counts = metadata.groupby(pd.Grouper(key = 'First_Publication_Date', freq = 'M')).size() 
axs[0].bar(counts.index, counts.values, width = 25, color = '#aaaaaa') 

## Line plot for sequencing cost over time 
ax = axs[0].twinx() 

ax.set_ylabel('Cost per Mb', fontsize = 8) 
ax.set_yscale('log') 
ax.get_yaxis().get_major_formatter().useOffset = False 
ax.plot(sequencing_costs.Date, sequencing_costs['Cost per Mb'], 
        linewidth = 0.5, 
        linestyle = '--', 
        color = 'black') 

## Scatter plot Contig N50 with respect to first publication date 
axs[1].set_ylabel('Contig N50', fontsize = 8) 
axs[1].set_yscale('log') 

for sequencing_type in ('No information provided', 'Short read', 'Long read'): 
    axs[1].scatter(x = metadata.loc[metadata.Sequencing_Type == sequencing_type, 'First_Publication_Date'], 
               y = metadata.loc[metadata.Sequencing_Type == sequencing_type, 'Original_Contig_N50'], 
               c = color_map[sequencing_type], 
               marker = 'o', s = 50, 
               edgecolors = 'black', 
               linewidths = 0.4) 

ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)
axs[0].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)
axs[1].tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=7)

## Create annotations for the list of accessions specified above 
annotations = [] 
for accession in accessions_to_label: 
    line = metadata.loc[accession]
    date = line['First_Publication_Date']
    value = line['Original_Contig_N50'] 
    label = line['Organism_Name'] 
    
    annotations.append(axs[1].annotate(label, (date, value), 
                                       style = 'italic', 
                                       color = 'black', 
                                       size = 6, 
                                       ha = 'left', 
                                       va = 'bottom'))
